_meanings:
(Connected with the
Prākṛta {#laqaha#} which appears to be
derived from it) Charming, 
handsome, beautiful, attractive, lovely;
{#atikrAMtaH kAlo lawaBalalanABogasulaBaH#}
<ls>Bh. 3. 32</ls> (where commentators
render {#lawaBa#} by {#salAvaRya#}); {#tasyAH#} 
{#pAdanaKaSreRiH SoBate lawaBaBuvaH#} <ls>Vikr. 8. 6.</ls>
Bilhaṇa has used this word in
three more places of the same book, 

where it appears to mean ‘a young
pretty woman’, ‘a handsome 
woman’; {%<ab>e. g.</ab>%} {#kiM vA varRanayA#} 
{#samastalawaBAlaMkAratAmezyati#} <ls n="Vikr.">8. 86</ls>;  
{#anarGyalAvaRyaniDAnaBUmirna kasya loBaM lawaBA tanoti#} <ls n="Vikr.">9. 68</ls>;
{#keSabaMDaviBabErlawaBAnAM piMqatAmiva jagAma#}
{#tamisraM#} <ls n="Vikr.">11. 18.</ls>
